    "Recall the definition of ε π k in ( 15).E[ε π k+1 -ε π k] = E[J f (π θ k, ϕ ω k, μk) -J f (π θ k, ϕ ω k+1, μk+1)] + E[J f (π θ k, ϕ ω k+1, μk+1) -J f (π θ k+1, ϕ ω k+1, μk+1)] + E[J f (π ⋆ (ϕ ω k+1, μk+1), ϕ ω k+1, μk+1) -J f (π ⋆ (ϕ ω k, μk), ϕ ω k, μk)] ≤ (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k 4|S| E[∥π ⋆ (ϕ ω k, μk) -π θ k ∥ 2] + 2|S|L 2 V L 2 D L 2 H ξ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[∥π ⋆ (ϕ ω k,μ k) -π θ k ∥ 2] + 2|S|L 2 V η 2 2 ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[ε ϕ k] + 16|S|L 2 L 4 V L 2 D L 2 H ξ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[ε µ k] + 8|S|L 2 V ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[ε V l,k] + L V (∥ω k+1 -ω k ∥ 2 + ∥μ k+1 -μk ∥ 2) - α k 16 E[∥∇ θ J f (π θ k, ϕ ω k, μk)∥ 2] + 2L 2 V α k E[ε V f,k] + 3L 2 V ξ 2 k + 2B F (B D + B H)α k ξ k - 3(1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k 8|S| ∥π ⋆ (ϕ ω k, μk) -π θ k ∥ 2 ≤ - α k 16 E[∥∇ θ J f (π θ k, ϕ ω k, μk)∥ 2] + 2L 2 V α k E[ε V f,k] + 2|S|L 2 V η 2 2 ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[ε ϕ k] + 16|S|L 2 L 4 V L 2 D L 2 H ξ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[ε µ k] + 8|S|L 2 V ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[ε V l,k] + 3L 2 V ξ 2 k + 2B F (B D + B H)α k ξ k + L V (B 2 D ζ 2 k + B 2 H ξ 2 k) ≤ - α k 16 E[∥∇ θ J f (π θ k, ϕ ω k, μk)∥ 2] + 2|S|L 2 V η 2 2 ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[ε ϕ k] + 16|S|L 2 L 4 V L 2 D L 2 H ξ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[ε µ k] + 8|S|L 2 V ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[ε V l,k] + 2L 2 V α k E[ε V f,k] + 3B F (B D + B H)α k ξ k,where the second inequality uses the step size condition ξ k α k ≤(1-γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min 4|S|L V L D L H, and the last inequality is due to the step size conditionζ k ξ k ≤ B H B D and ξ k α k ≤ B F (B D +B H) L V (2B 2 H +3L V).",
    "■ C.4 Proof of Proposition 4We introduce a technical lemma below, which bounds an important cross term in the proof of the proposition.Lemma 7 Under the assumptions and step sizes of Proposition 4, we have for all k ≥ 0E[⟨ Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f + β k Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k), V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f -V π θ k+1,ϕω k+1, μk+1 f ⟩] ≤ (1 -γ)β k 2 E[∥ Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f + β k Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k)∥ 2] + 6L 2 V α 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[∥∇ θ J f (π θ k, ϕ ω k, μk)∥ 2] + 6L 2 V L 2 H ξ 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε π k] + 6L 2 V η 2 2 ζ 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε ϕ k] + 16L 2 L 2 V L 2 H ξ 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε µ k] + 6L 4 V ζ 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε V f,k] + 24L 2 V L 2 D α 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε V l,k] + L V V (B F + B D + B H) 2 α 2 k.The proof of the lemma can be found in Section D.7.By the definition of ε V f,k and the update rule Vf,k,ε V f,k+1 = ∥ Vf,k+1 -V π θ k+1,ϕω k+1, μk+1 f ∥ 2 = ∥Π B V Vf,k + β k G f (θ k, μk, Vf,k, s k, a k, b k, s ′ k) -V π θ k+1,ϕω k+1, μk+1 f ∥ 2 ≤ Vf,k + β k G f (θ k, μk, Vf,k, s k, a k, b k, s ′ k) -V π θ k+1,ϕω k+1, μk+1 f 2 = Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f + β k Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k) + β k G f (θ k, μk, Vf,k, s k, a k, b k, s ′ k) -Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k) + V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f -V π θ k+1,ϕω k+1, μk+1 f 2 ≤ Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f + β k Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k) 2 + 2β 2 k ∥G f (θ k, μk, Vf,k, s k, a k, b k, s ′ k) -Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k)∥ 2 + 2 V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f -V π θ k+1,ϕω k+1, μk+1 f 2 + β k ⟨ Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f + β k Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k), G f (θ k, μk, Vf,k, s k, a k, b k, s ′ k) -Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k)⟩ + ⟨ Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f + β k Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k), V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f -V π θ k+1,ϕω k+1, μk+1 f ⟩, (65)where the first inequality follows from the fact that the projection to a convex set is non-expansive.To bound the first term of (65),Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f + β k Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k) 2 = ∥ Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f ∥ 2 + β 2 k ∥ Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k)∥ 2 + 2β k ⟨ Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f, Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k)⟩ = ∥ Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f ∥ 2 + β 2 k ∥ Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k) -Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f)∥ 2 + 2β k ⟨ Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f, Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k) -Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f)⟩ = ∥ Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f ∥ 2 + β 2 k ∥ Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k) -Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f)∥ 2 + 2β k Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f ⊤ (γP π θ k,ϕω k, μk -I) Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f ≤ ∥ Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f ∥ 2 + L 2 G β 2 k ∥ Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f ∥ 2 + 2(γ -1)β k ∥ Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f ∥ 2 ≤ (1 -(1 -γ)β k)ε V f,k,(66)where the last inequality follows from the step size conditionβ k ≤ 1-γ L 2 G.For the third term of (65),2∥V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f -V π θ k+1,ϕω k+1, μk+1 f ∥ 2 ≤ 6L 2 V ∥π θ k+1 -π θ k ∥ 2 + ∥ϕ ω k+1 -ϕ ω k ∥ 2 + ∥μ k+1 -μk ∥ 2 2 ≤ 6L 2 V B 2 F α 2 k + B 2 D ζ 2 k + B 2 H ξ 2 k ≤ 6L 2 V (B F + B D + B H) 2 α 2 k.(67)Note that the fourth term of (65) vanishes in expectation.",
    "Collecting the bounds from ( 66), (67), and Lemma 7, we haveE[ε V f,k+1] ≤ (1 -(1 -γ)β k)E[ε V f,k] + 2β 2 k E[∥G f (θ k, μk, Vf,k, s k, a k, b k, s ′ k) -Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k)∥ 2] + 6L 2 V (B F + B D + B H) 2 α 2 k + (1 -γ)β k 2 E[∥ Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f + β k Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k)∥ 2] + 6L 2 V α 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[∥∇ θ J f (π θ k, ϕ ω k, μk)∥ 2] + 6L 2 V L 2 H ξ 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε π k] + 6L 2 V η 2 2 ζ 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε ϕ k] + 16L 2 L 2 V L 2 H ξ 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε µ k] + 6L 4 V ζ 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε V f,k] + 24L 2 V L 2 D α 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε V l,k] + L V V (B F + B D + B H) 2 α 2 k ≤ (1 - (1 -γ)β k 2 + 6L 4 V ζ 2 k (1 -γ)β k)E[ε V f,k] + 8B 2 G β 2 k + (6L 2 V + L V V)(B F + B D + B H) 2 α 2 k + 6L 2 V α 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[∥∇ θ J f (π θ k, ϕ ω k, μk)∥ 2] + 6L 2 V L 2 H ξ 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε π k] + 6L 2 V η 2 2 ζ 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε ϕ k] + 16L 2 L 2 V L 2 H ξ 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε µ k] + 24L 2 V L 2 D α 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε V l,k] ≤ (1 - (1 -γ)β k 4)E[ε V f,k] + 6L 2 V α 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[∥∇ θ J f (π θ k, ϕ ω k, μk)∥ 2] + 6L 2 V L 2 H ξ 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε π k] + 6L 2 V η 2 2 ζ 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε ϕ k] + 16L 2 L 2 V L 2 H ξ 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε µ k] + 24L 2 V L 2 D α 2 k (1 -γ)β k E[ε V l,k] + 12B 2 G β 2 k,where the second inequality follows from ∥ Vf,k -Vπ θ k,ϕω k, μk f + β k Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k)∥ 2 ≤ ε V f,kestablished in (66), and the last inequality follows from the step size conditionsζ k β k ≤ 1-γ 2 √ 6L 2 V and α k β k ≤ 2B G √ 6L 2 V +L V V (B F +B D +B H).The bound on E[ε V l,k] can be established using an identical argument, under the step size conditionα k β k ≤ 1-γ 4 √ 6L V L D. ■ D Proof of Lemmas D.1 Proof of Lemma 1We focus on proving the inequalities under the follower's reward and note that the same argument can be used for the leader's cumulative reward and value function.We show the Lipschitz continuity conditions first.",
    "Fixing the mean field and leader's policy, the follower's problem reduces to a standard infinite-horizon discounted-reward MDP, in which it is well-known that the value function is Lipschitz and smooth with respect to the follower's policy parameter.",
    "Specifically, adapting Zeng et al. [2021][Lemma B.5], we have∥V π θ,ϕω,µ f -V π θ ′,ϕ ω ′,µ f ∥ ≤ 2 (1 -γ) 2 (∥θ -θ ′ ∥ + ∥ϕ ω -ϕ ω ′ ∥)."
